thread.title: Grain Mostly higher, livestock lower

title: Grain Mostly higher, livestock lower
text:
Thu, Aug 6, 2015, 1:45 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 8 hrs 15 mins Grain Mostly higher, livestock lower Grain mostly higher on the CBOT, beef and pork lower on the CME Associated Press – 1 hour 11 minutes ago Recommend Print 
CHICAGO (AP) -- Grain futures were mostly higher in early trading Tuesday on the Chicago Board of Trade. 
Wheat for September delivery rose 5 cents to $4.9860 a bushel; December corn was 4 cents higher at $3.83 a bushel; December oats were 1 cent lower at $2.4420 bushel; while November soybeans gained 12 cents to 9.5420 cents a bushel. 
Beef and pork were lower on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. 
October live cattle was .25 cent lower at $1.4795 a pound; August feeder cattle was .23 cent lower at $2.1373 a pound; October lean hogs lost .88 cent to $.6648 a pound. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Lizard and snake halt huge $16.5b Qld mine AAP
